                   "message":  "W08-ACCELERATOR-DOC-RECONCILE: record #308-#311 (File/Edit accelerator EXECUTION), docs-only\n\nForward-only state-doc reconcile. The W08 accelerator-EXECUTION code thread is\ncomplete at e98f41d (#308-#311), but the live state docs still stopped at #304/#305\nand described accelerators as display-only with W08 EXECUTION deferred.\n\nRecords that #308-#311 shipped File/Edit accelerator EXECUTION:\n- #308 (453a569, W08-CANONICAL-MENU-SOURCE) — default editor menu moved into\n  editor-ui (default_editor_menu) + ResolveResult::command_for_shortcut.\n- #309 (9004b4b, W08-2-KEYCODE-PARITY) — shell-local keycode_to_shortcut + parity\n  guard; no live-path change.\n- #310 (4fc66cf, W08-3-KEYSTROKE-CUTOVER) — live cutover: window_event resolves a\n  keystroke via keycode_to_shortcut -\u003e command_for_shortcut -\u003e route_menu_command.\n- #311 (e98f41d, W08-4-RETIRE-SHADOW) — retired the EditorKeyCommand File/Edit\n  shadow binds; re-anchored the parity guard (menu canonical, no shadow).\n\nSupersedes the #304 snapshot\u0027s \"mirror the live EditorKeyCommand::from_key_press\nrouting\" + \"W08 EXECUTION will unify the two\" framing (the menu is now the SOURCE\nof that routing) and narrows its \"Still deferred: accelerator-table EXECUTION\"\nline (File/Edit EXECUTION half shipped).\n\nDeferred list narrowed CAREFULLY (NOT claimed done): Play/View accelerator\ndisplay+execution, AcceleratorTable conflict UI/population, registry-driven\ndynamic predicates + per-frame re-resolve, dynamic toggle labels, plugin menu\nentries, host-\u003eshell FIFO menu-click replacement (the keyboard was unified onto\nroute_menu_command; the click FIFO was NOT replaced), and generalized command\nexecution beyond the five File/Edit binds. Time-scale (Ctrl+2/0/4), Space/Escape\nplayback, and plain-R reload stay execution-only keybinds with no menu home\n(intentional asymmetry).\n\nForward-only: Status.md + HANDOFF.md prepend a new top snapshot; plans/BASELINE.md\ninserts a new subsection ABOVE the #304/#305 one; change.md appends a new entry.\nHistorical snapshots/subsections preserved byte-identical.\n\nDocs only (4 files); no Rust source / test / Cargo change.\nGate: VERIFY OK 7/7 + 10/10 arch lints (Markdown-only, no Rust touched).\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) \u003cnoreply@anthropic.com\u003e",
